    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the spindle assembly checkpoint fails and the cell prematurely enters Anaphase, the result can be catastrophic. In this scenario, known as aneuploidy, some chromosomes may not segregate evenly, meaning one daughter cell may receive extra chromosomes while another gets deficient. This chromosomal imbalance disrupts normal cell function, leading to cell death or disease conditions, such as certain types of cancer. Proper checkpoint regulation is essential for maintaining genetic stability and ensuring accurate cell division.",
